President Biden addressed a crowd at the White House, thanking them for their support and celebrating the passage of the Inflation Reduction Act. He emphasized that the law will benefit the American people and hold corporations accountable. The President highlighted the provisions of the law that will lower prescription drug costs, health insurance costs, and energy costs for families. He also discussed the aggressive action the law takes to combat the climate crisis and increase energy security. President Biden expressed his commitment to American workers and companies, stating that the future will be built in the United States. He criticized Republicans for opposing the law and outlined their plans to repeal it if they regain control of Congress. The President reassured the audience that no one earning less than $400,000 a year will pay more in federal taxes. He emphasized the progress his administration has made in job creation, infrastructure investment, gun safety, veterans' healthcare, and technology development. President Biden concluded by expressing his optimism about America's future and urging unity and determination to overcome the challenges facing the country.